This article is a statement by the President of the United States on the 15th anniversary of the genocide at Srebrenica. The President expresses his condolences and reflects on the tragedy of the 8,000 men and boys who were killed during the genocide. He acknowledges that the international community failed to protect them and emphasizes the need for justice and accountability for the crimes that occurred. The President calls for the arrest and prosecution of those responsible, including Ratko Mladic, who remains at large. He also highlights the importance of remembering the cruelty that occurred and preventing such atrocities from happening again.